tter, trays will be your best friend. Creating contained drop zones will prevent visual overwhelm. A simple yet effective tool is to use an open basket to store hats and scarves. Sometimes that makeup bag can be a real clutter hotspot. Instead, consider storing your everyday makeup in a vanity organizer that fits perfectly in your medicine cabinet. And this will free up a lot of space on your counters. Use automatic soap dispensers that are free of loud packaging and labels. As a rule, try to display only the things that you find beautiful to look at. The more practical everyday items you can store away. And as you can see here, I do like to make my life easier by storing all-purpose cleaner close to where I need to use it. And speaking of really microscopic visual clutter, are you guys familiar with the eye level test? This is a very simple test of how clean a surface really is. And speaking of surfaces, for all the pet parents out there, I love to keep a lint roller handy, especially in the summer when Sweetie is in major shedding mode."}, {"shortCode": "Da0lp2bSsQ-", "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/Da0lp2bSsQ-/", "caption": "Things to get rid of in your bedroom that are disrupting your peace #home #bedroom #homeorganization #declutter #tidy @therealreal", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T17:23:02.000Z", "videoDuration": 59.666, "videoPlayCount": 12673, "videoViewCount": null, "likesCount": 172, "commentsCount": 0, "displayUrl": "https://scontent-atl3-3.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/748026107_18120486538828197_516046116589266571_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-atl3-3.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=109&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gErUiN75Bf7SiAPcN74MhmzuuJDQa-yk164iCih7wUef1Y4ivVfO8MMduCwoelIIm8&_nc_ohc=UfmjS7ecuMwQ7kNvwHiU4s9&_nc_gid=Alz0SiQsKPxAurUavF9oHw&edm=ADp7STQBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AQAo89DHDYSrkDx4wKYBeBpKDVaf08Y9PrcN-e_2zLZ7zw&oe=6A61B440&_nc_sid=c6f216", "videoUrl": "https://scontent-mia3-2.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m86/AQNY4MeLS9Vqtn5cpfb1cc9qOgdR_-erqOHhlNz5jPGQii39N